sparql_query_kg2:
To produce the SPARQL query for KG2 (DBpedia) based on the given information, we need to map the Wikidata entities and relations to their corresponding DBpedia entities and relations. 

Given the Entity and Relation Mapping (ER2):

[
  {
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein",
    "wikidata_ids": [
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q937"
    ]
  },
  {
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/doctoralAdvisor",
    "wikidata_ids": [
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P184"
    ]
  }
]

We need to map the Wikidata entity Q937 to its DBpedia equivalent, which is http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein. We also need to map the Wikidata property P184 to its DBpedia equivalent, which is http://dbpedia.org/ontology/doctoralAdvisor.

The SPARQL query for KG2 (DBpedia) should be:

<sparql>
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/> 
PREFIX res: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/> 
SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE { res:Albert_Einstein dbo:doctoralAdvisor ?uri }
</sparql>

This query selects the entity that is the doctoral advisor of Albert Einstein.

